cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with decoding motor actions from local field potentials (LFP) activity in the pre-frontal cortex. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel pre-processing technique for adapting the feature space of the source to the destination. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with brain-computer interfacing. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible category as the experiment involves memory-guided visual saccades to target locations. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely as there is no mention of sound or audio in the paper.
